# Contentful CMS & Blog Patterns

## CMS Architecture

Blog content is managed in **Contentful CMS** and fetched at build/request time via the Contentful Delivery API.

### Client Setup (`lib/contentful.ts`)

Two clients are available:

- **`client`** — Standard delivery API (published content only)
- **`previewClient`** — Preview API (includes draft content, used when `CONTENTFUL_PREVIEW_TOKEN` is set)

### Environment Variables

```env
CONTENTFUL_SPACE_ID=          # Contentful space ID
CONTENTFUL_ACCESS_TOKEN=      # Delivery API token
CONTENTFUL_PREVIEW_TOKEN=     # Preview API token (optional)
```

---

## Blog Service (`services/blogService.ts`)

All blog data fetching goes through `blogService`:

### `blogService.getAllPosts()`

- Fetches all published blog posts from Contentful
- Sorted by `publishedDate` descending
- Returns array of `BlogPost` objects
- Falls back to placeholder images if Contentful asset is missing

### `blogService.getPostBySlug(slug)`

- Fetches a single blog post by slug
- Handles inconsistent slug formats (normalizes leading slashes and `/blog/` prefix)
- Returns `null` if not found
- Includes rich text `content` field for rendering

### BlogPost Type

```tsx
interface BlogPost {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  slug: string;
  category: "Guides" | "Industry" | "Company";
  date: string;
  author: string;
  image: string;
  description: string;
  content?: Document; // Rich text (only on detail pages)
}
```

